A Health-e investigation into the now deregistered doctor's gruesome actions, aired on eNCA's Checkpoint last year. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There has been some reprieve for families affected by the botched work of Potchefstroom general practitioner David Sello. The Health Professions Council of South Africa found Sello guilty on all 26 counts brought against him. READ: The NHI will help everyone: Mkhize He was found guilty of misconduct involving three deaths and two patients who were disfigured and live in pain following his procedures. His medical licence has also been revoked. Checkpoint and Health-e first broke the story in March 2018 detailing unorthodox and complex procedures being performed in his consulting rooms in Ikageng.